  "elements": [
    {
      "id": "ykZadHFIh9AKVNgaeENUh",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -3927.8493893730724,
      "y": -3806.4038568704727,
      "width": 1510.9989013671875,
      "height": 1200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#6741d9",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0z",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1180471415,
      "version": 3186,
      "versionNonce": 987135321,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1773669276490,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Flight booking system\n1. User should be able to view upcoming flights (some random fare), with multiple date, price etc.. filters\n2. User should be able to book a flight (assume a static set of seats, 30 (A-F))\n    a. customer details on a new page after book flight clicked\n    b. customer will select the seats from the seatmap, (reserve the seat for 10 mins)\n    c. all metadata related to booking is stored, assuming we get a callback for that particular booking after t time\n        1. payment confirmed\n        2. payment cancelled\n        3. payment declined\n        4. payment pending (confirm for first 10 minutes, after revert the transaction)\n    d. payment system is a blackbox, no money movement flows are to be included\n    e. Once payment is confirmed, block the seats\n3. Multiple seats can be booked in a single booking\n4. Block the seats when the customer selects the seat for 10 minutes\n\nOut of scope\n1. Ticket creations, communcations\n2. Payment gateway integration\n\n\n\nEntites - \n    Flights\n    Users \n    Seatmap\n    BookingIntent (seat details, user id, payment, bookingIntentId, retryCount, status, paymentIntentIDs[a,b])\n    PaymentStatus (bookingIntentId, payment status)\n \n    \n    \n       \n    status enums - IN_PROGRESS, REJECTED, DECLINED, ACCEPTED\n    \n    \n\n\n1. didn;t receive payment confirmation for 9 mintues\n2. we will give option to the user after 5 minutes, if he wants to try the payment (extend the reserved window by 10 mins)\n3. second payment intent is created (second payment attempt by the user)\n4. book flight for first success payment\n    q. revert all success payments after this\n    b. if we receive callback at the same time for a booking intent id, can use redis distributed locking to ensure not two transactions try to attempt\n         the booking entity (status)\n    c. first failed (check if there are multiple intents present, no status changes if still awaiting on payment status) , then second success\n\n\n\n    ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Flight booking system\n1. User should be able to view upcoming flights (some random fare), with multiple date, price etc.. filters\n2. User should be able to book a flight (assume a static set of seats, 30 (A-F))\n    a. customer details on a new page after book flight clicked\n    b. customer will select the seats from the seatmap, (reserve the seat for 10 mins)\n    c. all metadata related to booking is stored, assuming we get a callback for that particular booking after t time\n        1. payment confirmed\n        2. payment cancelled\n        3. payment declined\n        4. payment pending (confirm for first 10 minutes, after revert the transaction)\n    d. payment system is a blackbox, no money movement flows are to be included\n    e. Once payment is confirmed, block the seats\n3. Multiple seats can be booked in a single booking\n4. Block the seats when the customer selects the seat for 10 minutes\n\nOut of scope\n1. Ticket creations, communcations\n2. Payment gateway integration\n\n\n\nEntites - \n    Flights\n    Users \n    Seatmap\n    BookingIntent (seat details, user id, payment, bookingIntentId, retryCount, status, paymentIntentIDs[a,b])\n    PaymentStatus (bookingIntentId, payment status)\n \n    \n    \n       \n    status enums - IN_PROGRESS, REJECTED, DECLINED, ACCEPTED\n    \n    \n\n\n1. didn;t receive payment confirmation for 9 mintues\n2. we will give option to the user after 5 minutes, if he wants to try the payment (extend the reserved window by 10 mins)\n3. second payment intent is created (second payment attempt by the user)\n4. book flight for first success payment\n    q. revert all success payments after this\n    b. if we receive callback at the same time for a booking intent id, can use redis distributed locking to ensure not two transactions try to attempt\n         the booking entity (status)\n    c. first failed (check if there are multiple intents present, no status changes if still awaiting on payment status) , then second success\n\n\n\n    ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
